%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsundar-pichai-google-alphabet-ceo-career-life%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle%20CEO%20Sundar%20Pichai%3C%2Fa%3E%20referred%20to%20this%20phase%20of%20AI%20as%20AJI%2C%20or%20%26quot%3Bartificial%20jagged%20intelligence%2C%26quot%3B%20on%20a%20recent%20episode%20of%20Lex%20Fridman's%20podcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20who%20used%20it%20first%2C%20maybe%20Karpathy%20did%2C%26quot%3B%20Pichai%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20deep%20learning%20and%20computer%20vision%20specialist%20Andrej%20Karpathy%2C%20who%20cofounded%20OpenAI%20before%20leaving%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAJI%20is%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20metaphor%20for%20the%20trajectory%20of%20AI%20development%20%E2%80%94%20jagged%2C%20marked%20at%20once%20by%20sparks%20of%20genius%20and%20basic%20mistakes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202024%20X%20post%20titled%20%26quot%3BJagged%20Intelligence%2C%26quot%3B%20Karpathy%20described%20the%20term%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bword%20I%20came%20up%20with%20to%20describe%20the%20(strange%2C%20unintuitive)%20fact%20that%20state%20of%20the%20art%20LLMs%20can%20both%20perform%20extremely%20impressive%20tasks%20(e.g.%20solve%20complex%20math%20problems)%20while%20simultaneously%20struggle%20with%20some%20very%20dumb%20problems.%26quot%3B%20He%20then%20posted%20examples%20of%20state%20of%20the%20art%20large%20language%20models%20failing%20to%20understand%20that%209.9%20is%20bigger%20than%209.11%2C%20making%20%26quot%3Bnon-sensical%20decisions%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20game%20of%20tic-tac-toe%2C%20and%20struggling%20to%20count.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20is%20that%20unlike%20humans%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhere%20a%20lot%20of%20knowledge%20and%20problem-solving%20capabilities%20are%20all%20highly%20correlated%20and%20improve%20linearly%20all%20together%2C%20from%20birth%20to%20adulthood%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20jagged%20edges%20of%20AI%20are%20not%20always%20clear%20or%20predictable%2C%20Karpathy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPichai%20echoed%20the%20idea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20see%20what%20they%20can%20do%20and%20then%20you%20can%20trivially%20find%20they%20make%20numerical%20errors%20or%20counting%20R's%20in%20strawberry%20or%20something%2C%20which%20seems%20to%20trip%20up%20most%20models%2C%26quot%3B%20Pichai%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20we%20are%20in%20the%20AJI%20phase%20where%20dramatic%20progress%2C%20some%20things%20don't%20work%20well%2C%20but%20overall%2C%20you're%20seeing%20lots%20of%20progress.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202010%2C%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-deepmind%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20DeepMind%3C%2Fa%3E%20launched%2C%20its%20team%20would%20talk%20about%20a%2020-year%20timeline%20for%20AGI%2C%20Pichai%20said.%20Google%20subsequently%20acquired%20DeepMind%20in%202014.%20Pichai%20thinks%20it'll%20take%20a%20little%20longer%20than%20that%2C%20but%20by%202030%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20would%20stress%20it%20doesn't%20matter%20what%20that%20definition%20is%20because%20you%20will%20have%20mind-blowing%20progress%20on%20many%20dimensions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20then%20the%20world%20will%20also%20need%20a%20clear%20system%20for%20labeling%20AI-generated%20content%20to%20%26quot%3Bdistinguish%20reality%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BProgress%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20vague%20term%2C%20but%20Pichai%20has%20spoken%20at%20length%20about%20the%20benefits%20we'll%20see%20from%20AI%20development.%20At%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ceo-sundar-pichai-un-summit-future-ai-advance-humanity-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUN's%20Summit%20of%20the%20Future%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20September%202024%2C%20he%20outlined%20four%20specific%20ways%20that%20AI%20would%20advance%20humanity%20%E2%80%94%20improving%20access%20to%20knowledge%20in%20native%20languages%2C%20accelerating%20scientific%20discovery%2C%20mitigating%20climate%20disaster%2C%20and%20contributin