C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehardest%20part%20of%20their%20death%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20was%20having%20to%20tell%20my%20kids%20who%20were%20very%20close%20to%20Gram%20and%20Gramps.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225b5311a6-cdf0-4dd2-a146-2bb8b8de7992%5C%22%3EThey%20struggled%20with%20the%20loss%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20kids%20watched%20my%20grandparents%20through%20their%20respective%20health%20battles.%20Once%2C%20my%20grandmother%20fainted%20during%20one%20of%20their%20birthday%20parties%2C%20and%20we%20had%20to%20rush%20her%20by%20ambulance%20to%20the%20hospital.%20Another%20time%2C%20we%20spent%20a%20Thanksgiving%20visit%20wondering%20if%20my%20grandfather%20would%20wake%20up%20from%20a%20cardiac%20event%20he%20endured%20after%20surgery%20for%20throat%20cancer.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20kids%20knew%20about%20long-term%20illness%20as%20much%20as%20children%20could.%20Death%20was%20different%2C%20though.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworried-how-to-share-bad-news-with-kids-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20two%20oldest%20struggled%20with%20the%20loss%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Thankfully%2C%20the%20two%20youngest%20were%20too%20young%20to%20understand.%20I%20took%20the%20oldest%20to%20my%20grandfather's%20funeral%2C%20thinking%20it%20might%20help%20them%20process%20the%20loss%20of%20a%20man%20they%20had%20known%20their%20whole%20lives.%20Bagpipes%20played%20as%20we%20entered%20the%20church%2C%20and%20on%20the%20ride%20home%2C%20I%20listened%20to%20my%20kids%20cry%20in%20the%20back%20seat.%20We%20stayed%20in%20the%20apartment%20Gram%20had%20shared%20with%20Gramps.%20We%20ate%20Chinese%20food%20from%20our%20favorite%20place%20and%20stared%20at%20his%20seat%20on%20the%20couch%20that%20would%20remain%20forever%20empty.%20My%20grandmother%20was%20in%20an%20assisted%20care%20facility%20by%20this%20time.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C